# Production Environment Variables
# Copy to .env.production and fill in values
#
# This file is loaded by Docker Compose via the env_file directive.
# The postgres service uses POSTGRES_PASSWORD to initialize the database.
#
# CRITICAL: POSTGRES_PASSWORD must match the password in api/.env.production DATABASE_URL
#
# Password Synchronization Example:
#   1. Generate a strong password once:
#      PGPASS=$(openssl rand -base64 32)
#   2. Use the SAME password in both files:
#      - Here: POSTGRES_PASSWORD=your_strong_password_here
#      - In api/.env.production: DATABASE_URL=postgresql://vacay:your_strong_password_here@postgres:5432/vacay
#
# Run with: docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml --env-file .env.production up -d
# (Note: --env-file is now optional since docker-compose.prod.yml includes env_file directive)

# ============================================
# REQUIRED - Database
# ============================================
# IMPORTANT: This password MUST match the password in api/.env.production DATABASE_URL
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=generate_a_strong_password_here

# ============================================
# OPTIONAL - Remote Development via Tailscale
# ============================================
# Set to 0.0.0.0 to expose postgres on all interfaces (for Tailscale dev access)
# Default: 127.0.0.1 (localhost only - more secure)
# POSTGRES_HOST=0.0.0.0

# ============================================
# Note: API-specific variables go in api/.env.production
# See api/.env.example for the full list
# ============================================
